<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="735" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Ambassador of
                                    Austria-Hungary</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-10-22"><hi rend="italic">October 22,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Will you, as dean of the
                            diplomatic corps, be so kind as to name the honorary pallbearers to act
                            at the funeral of the late Don Jorge Muñoz, minister from Guatemala?</p>
                        <p>The funeral will take place at 10 o’clock a.m. on Wednesday, the 24th
                            instant, at St. Matthew’s Church</p>
                        <p>Faithfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>